	<h2 class="story">
		

		

		
		

		

		

		

		<span id="title-172869452" class="story-title"> <a   href="//apple.slashdot.org/story/24/01/26/1714204/apple-faces-strong-action-if-app-store-changes-fall-short-eus-breton-says">Apple Faces 'Strong Action' If App Store Changes Fall Short, EU's Breton Says</a> <span class=" no extlnk"><a class="story-sourcelnk" href="https://www.reuters.com/technology/apple-faces-strong-action-if-app-store-changes-fall-short-eus-breton-says-2024-01-26/"  title="External link - https://www.reuters.com/technology/apple-faces-strong-action-if-app-store-changes-fall-short-eus-breton-says-2024-01-26/" target="_blank"> (reuters.com) </a></span></span>

		
		
		<!--<span class="comments commentcnt-172869452" >60</span>-->
		

		
		<!-- comment bubble -->
		
			<span class="comment-bubble"><a href="//apple.slashdot.org/story/24/01/26/1714204/apple-faces-strong-action-if-app-store-changes-fall-short-eus-breton-says#comments" title="">60</a></span>
		
	</h2>
	<div class="details" id="details-172869452">
		<span class="story-details">
		<span class="story-views">
			<span class="sodify" onclick="firehose_set_options('color', 'red')" title="Filter Firehose to entries rated red or better"></span><span class="icon-beaker pop1 " alt="Popularity" title="Filter Firehose to entries rated red or better" onclick="firehose_set_options('color', 'red')"><span></span></span> 
		</span>
		</span>
		<span class="story-byline">
	
				
			Posted
				by 
		
		
			
				  msmash
			
		
		

		
		
		<time id="fhtime-172869452" datetime="on Friday January 26, 2024 @01:01PM">on Friday January 26, 2024 @01:01PM</time>
		
		
			 from the <span class="dept-text">warning-issued</span> dept.
		
		</span>
	</div>
</header>

<div class="body" id="fhbody-172869452">
	
		
	

	
		
		<div id="text-172869452" class="p">
			
		 	
				Apple <a href="https://www.reuters.com/technology/apple-faces-strong-action-if-app-store-changes-fall-short-eus-breton-says-2024-01-26/">faces strong action</a> if <a href="https://apple.slashdot.org/story/24/01/25/2059255/apple-is-bringing-sideloading-and-alternate-app-stores-to-the-iphone">changes to its App Store</a> do not meet incoming European Union regulations, the bloc's industry chief said on Friday. Reuters:<i> In a move designed to comply with the EU's incoming Digital Markets Act (DMA), the company will soon allow software developers to distribute their apps to Apple devices via alternative stores. From early March, developers will be able to offer alternative app stores on iPhones and opt out of using Apple's in-app payment system, which charges commissions of up to 30%.<br> <br>

However, critics have said the changes <a href="https://apple.slashdot.org/story/24/01/26/140245/shameless-insult-malicious-compliance-junk-fees-extortion-regime-industry-reacts-to-apples-proposed-changes-over-digital-markets-act">do not go far enough</a>, arguing Apple's fee structure remains unfair, and that the changes may be in violation of the DMA. Asked about Apple's plans, EU industry chief Thierry Breton exclusively told Reuters: "The DMA will open the gates of the internet to competition so that digital markets are fair and open. Change is already happening. As from 7 March we will assess companies' proposals, with the feedback of third parties." He added: "If the proposed solutions are not good enough, we will not hesitate to take strong action."</i><br>
		 	
		</div>

		

		

		
			
		
	</div>
