		<div id="comment_body_64190168"><p><div class="quote"><p>These legal battles wouldn't be confined to Europe. Apple, as a publicly traded company, would face immediate legal challenges in the U.S., particularly from investors concerned about a sudden 25% drop in revenue. This is not just about market dynamics; it's a potential corporate governance crisis.</p></div><p>This is the key point.  A sudden drop in revenue would be followed by a sudden drop in the Apple stock price, which means a drop in bonuses for Apple execs.  Apple as a company may be willing to thumb their nose at Europe, but the decision makers certainly would never consider doing so if that meant taking a hit on their bonuses.</p></div>
